04432nmm a2200541Ia 9780520354081DE-B159720240328111612.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240328t20182018cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805203540817 a10.1525/97805203540812doi  a(DE-B1597)649223  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 7aART0190102bisacsh1 aSullivan/Vainker, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aArts of China, Sixth Edition, Revised and Expanded /cSullivan/Vainker; ed. by Michael Sullivan, Shelagh Vainker. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2018] 4c©2018  a1 online resource (376 p.) :b423 color images and 14 maps  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tMap -- tPreface to Sixth Edition -- tAfterthoughts -- tChronological Table of Dynasties and Modern Republics -- tReign Periods of the Ming and Qing Dynasties -- t1 Before the Dawn of History -- t2 The Early Bronze Age: Shang and Western Zhou -- t3 Eastern Zhou and the Period of the Warring States -- t4 The Qin and Han Dynasties -- t5 The Three Kingdoms and the Six Dynasties -- t6 The Sui and Tang Dynasties -- t7 The Five Dynasties and the Song Dynasty -- t8 The Yuan Dynasty -- t9 The Ming Dynasty -- t10 The Qing Dynasty -- t11 The Twentieth Century and Beyond -- tNotes -- tBooks for Reference and Further Reading -- tList of Maps and Illustrations -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aInternationally renowned and a crucial classroom text, The Arts of China has been revised and expanded by the late Michael Sullivan, with Shelagh Vainker. This new, sixth, edition has an emphasis on Chinese art history, not as an assemblage of related topics, but as a continuous story. With updated attributions and dating throughout and a revised bibliography, it reflects the latest archaeological discoveries, as well as giving increased attention to modern and contemporary art and to calligraphy throughout China's history, with additional discussions of work by women artists. Visual enhancements include all new maps, and approximately one hundred new color illustrations—bringing the total to well over four hundred color illustrations. Written in the engaging and lucid style that is Sullivan's hallmark, The Arts of China is readily accessible to general readers as well as to serious students of art history. Sullivan's approach remains true to the way the Chinese themselves view art, providing readers with a sense of the sweep of history through China's dynasties. This organizational strategy makes it easy for readers to understand the distinct characteristics of each period of art and to gain a clearer view of how Chinese art has changed in relation to its historical context. With many improvements that bring it fully up to date, The Arts of China will remain the most comprehensive and widely read introduction to the history of Chinese art.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4aArt. 4aAsian. 4aChinese. 7aART / Asian / Chinese.2bisacsh1 aSullivan, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVainker, Shelagh, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052029481340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035408140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520354081423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520354081/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles